</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-47_ pf-text-1"><strong>Disinfect</strong> - Apply a gentle antiseptic to any breaks in the skin to prevent infection.













</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-49_ pf-text-1"><strong>Cover </strong>- Dress the wound with a sterile bandage or plaster.















</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-51_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Bruises</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-53_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-54_ pf-text-1"><strong>Cold compress </strong>- Apply a cold pack to the bruise for 20 minutes to reduce swelling.










</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-56_ pf-text-1"><strong>Elevate</strong> - Keep the bruised area elevated to further reduce swelling.
















</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-58_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Sprains</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-60_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-61_ pf-text-1"><strong>Rest </strong>- Encourage the child to rest and avoid using the injured area.










</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-63_ pf-text-1"><strong>Ice</strong> - Apply ice to the injury for 20 minutes every hour to reduce pain and swelling.














</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-65_ pf-text-1"><strong>Compression </strong>- Use an elastic bandage for compression to support the area.
















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-67_ pf-text-1"><strong>Elevation </strong>- Elevate the injured part to decrease swelling.
















</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-69_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Best practices in first aid</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-71_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-72_ pf-text-1"><strong>Education</strong> - Regularly update first aid knowledge and skills through certified courses. The Mandatory Training Group offers comprehensive courses covering first aid techniques for children and babies.










